#Popular Pod Network Solutions for Kubernetes:

| CNI Plugin      | Features                        | Suitable For                  | Example Command                 |
| --------------- | ------------------------------- | ----------------------------- | ------------------------------- |
| **Flannel**     | Simple, lightweight             | Small/medium clusters         | `kubectl apply -f flannel.yaml` |
| **Calico**      | Advanced, network policies, BGP | Medium/large clusters, secure | `kubectl apply -f calico.yaml`  |
| **Weave Net**   | Automatic encryption, simple    | Easy setup, encryption needed | `kubectl apply -f weave.yaml`   |
| **Cilium**      | High security, eBPF powered     | Performance-critical systems  | `kubectl apply -f cilium.yaml`  |
| **Canal**       | Calico + Flannel hybrid         | Balanced performance & ease   | Custom YAML deployment          |
| **Kube-Router** | Native IP routing, firewalling  | Lightweight, network focused  | Custom YAML deployment          |

#How Pod Networks Work:

They assign unique IPs to each pod.

Enable communication across nodes.

Ensure Kubernetes services (ClusterIP, NodePort, etc.) can properly route traffic.


#âœ… Step-by-Step Deployment Guide for Cilium:

Cilium uses eBPF (Extended Berkeley Packet Filter) for high-performance networking and security.
Itâ€™s a modern and production-grade choice.

#ğŸ¯ Prerequisites:

âœ”ï¸ You have a working Kubernetes cluster (kubeadm installed)
âœ”ï¸ All nodes can communicate (ping works)
âœ”ï¸ Pods and services are not yet deployed (fresh network setup recommended)


#ğŸ›  Step 1: Install cilium-cli:

# On your master node
curl -L --remote-name-all https://github.com/cilium/cilium-cli/releases/latest/download/cilium-linux-amd64.tar.gz{,.sha256sum}
sha256sum --check cilium-linux-amd64.tar.gz.sha256sum
sudo tar xzvf cilium-linux-amd64.tar.gz -C /usr/local/bin
cilium version


#ğŸ›  Step 2: Install Helm (Required for Cilium Install)

>> curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/helm/helm/master/scripts/get-helm-3 | bash
helm version


#Install Cilium on Cluster:

cilium install


#Validate the Installation:

cilium status


#(Optional but Recommended) Enable Hubble (Service Visibility)

cilium hubble enable


#Install Hubble UI

cilium hubble ui


#Deploy a Test Pod to Verify

kubectl create deployment nginx --image=nginx
kubectl expose deployment nginx --port=80 --type=NodePort
kubectl get svc nginx


===================================================
#Full Shell Script to Automate Cilium Installation:
===================================================


nano install_cilium.sh

>> 

# =====================================
# Kubernetes Cilium CNI Automated Setup
# =====================================

set -e

echo "ğŸ” Step 1: Installing cilium-cli..."
curl -L --remote-name-all https://github.com/cilium/cilium-cli/releases/latest/download/cilium-linux-amd64.tar.gz{,.sha256sum}
sha256sum --check cilium-linux-amd64.tar.gz.sha256sum
sudo tar xzvf cilium-linux-amd64.tar.gz -C /usr/local/bin
rm -f cilium-linux-amd64.tar.gz cilium-linux-amd64.tar.gz.sha256sum

echo "âœ… cilium-cli installed successfully."

echo "ğŸ” Step 2: Installing Helm..."
curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/helm/helm/master/scripts/get-helm-3 | bash
echo "âœ… Helm installed successfully."

echo "ğŸš€ Step 3: Deploying Cilium to the Kubernetes cluster..."
cilium install

echo "â³ Waiting for Cilium to be ready..."
cilium status --wait

echo "âœ… Cilium installed and running!"

echo "ğŸ” Step 4: Enabling Hubble observability..."
cilium hubble enable

echo "ğŸš€ Step 5: Deploying Hubble UI..."
cilium hubble ui --wait

echo "âœ… Hubble UI is now available via port-forwarding."

echo "ğŸš€ Step 6: Starting Hubble UI port-forward in the background..."
nohup cilium hubble port-forward &>/dev/null &

echo "ğŸ‰ Setup Complete! Access Hubble UI at: http://localhost:12000"

echo "ğŸ“¦ Deploying test Nginx pod..."
kubectl create deployment nginx --image=nginx --replicas=2
kubectl expose deployment nginx --port=80 --type=NodePort

echo "â³ Waiting for Nginx pod to be ready..."
kubectl wait --for=condition=available --timeout=120s deployment/nginx

echo "âœ… Nginx deployment is ready."

echo "ğŸŒ Retrieve NodePort for testing:"
kubectl get svc nginx -o wide

echo "ğŸ¯ Test Access: curl <Node-IP>:<NodePort> from any machine that can reach the node."

echo "âœ… Cluster Networking, Hubble, and Test Pod deployed successfully."

>> 

chmod +x install_cilium.sh

./install_cilium.sh



